# Xlsform template

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
The XLSForm Template is a tool used for designing surveys and forms that are compatible with the ODK ecosystem, including Kobotoolbox.

## Purpose
This template is used to design surveys or forms using the XLSForm standard, ensuring they are interoperable and flexible for use in various data collection platforms.

## How it works
The template consists of four sheets: survey, choices, settings, and entities. It also includes a template sheet with common columns in bold and other possible columns in regular text. Users can make a copy of the template to edit and customize their forms.

## Requirements
Understanding of data collection and the XLSForm Standard is necessary to effectively use this tool.

## Reflections
Using Kobo and the ODK ecosystem has been fundamental across various data collection R&D activities, and using the XLSForm Template can improve overall data collection and analysis skills.
